cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper discusses the design principles of deep convolutional networks and proposes a new architecture called SimpNet. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the trade-off between computation/memory efficiency and accuracy, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The proposed architecture also involves the use of a new layer, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture on standard datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
